Model Performance\n> The `evaluate_model()` helper is defined here and **reused for LSTM evaluation**.","metadata":{}},{"id":"t15-code","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Shared Evaluation Helper (used for both models) ─────────────────────────────\ndef evaluate_model(y_true, y_pred, model_name='Model'):\n    y_true = y_true.flatten()\n    y_pred = y_pred.flatten()\n\n    mae   = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)\n    mse   = mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred)\n    rmse  = np.sqrt(mse)\n    mape  = np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / np.where(y_true == 0, 1e-8, y_true))) * 100\n    ss_res = np.sum((y_true - y_pred) ** 2)\n    ss_tot = np.sum((y_true - y_true.mean()) ** 2)\n    r2    = 1 - ss_res / ss_tot\n\n    print(f'\\n{\"=\"*48}')\n    print(f'  {model_name} — Test Set Performance')\n    print(f'{\"=\"*48}')\n    print(f'  MAE   : {mae:>10.4f}  USD')\n    print(f'  RMSE  : {rmse:>10.4f}  USD')\n    print(f'  MSE   : {mse:>10.4f}')\n    print(f'  MAPE  : {mape:>10.2f}  %')\n    print(f'  R²    : {r2:>10.4f}')\n    print(f'{\"=\"*48}')\n\n    return {'MAE': mae, 'RMSE': rmse, 'MSE': mse, 'MAPE': mape, 'R2': r2}\n\n\n# ── Transformer Step 15: Evaluate ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nmetrics_t = evaluate_model(y_test_orig, y_pred_t, 'Transformer')\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-23T05:04:47.790687Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-23T05:04:47.791281Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-23T05:04:47.799576Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-23T05:04:47.791255Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-23T05:04:47.798778Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\n================================================\n  Transformer — Test Set Performance\n================================================\n  MAE   :     7.9806  USD\n  RMSE  :     9.6939  USD\n  MSE   :    93.9726\n  MAPE  :       3.88  %\n  R²    :     0.8423\n================================================\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":57},{"id":"t16-hdr","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Transformer Step 16 — Visualise Actual vs Predicted","metadata":{}},{"id":"t16-code","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Transformer Step 16: Visualise Actual vs Predicted ─────────────────────────\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(14, 10))\nfig.suptitle('Transformer — AAPL Close Price: Actual vs Predicted',\n             fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n\n# Full test set\naxes[0].plot(dates_test, y_test_orig,  label='Actual',    color='#1565C0', linewidth=1.1, alpha=0.9)\naxes[0].plot(dates_test, y_pred_t,     label='Predicted', color='#E65100', linewidth=1.1,\n             linestyle='--', alpha=0.9)\naxes[0].fill_between(dates_test,\n                     y_test_orig.flatten(), y_pred_t.flatten(),\n                     alpha=0.12, color='#E65100')\naxes[0].set_title(f'Full Test Set ({len(dates_test)} trading days)')\naxes[0].set_ylabel('AAPL Close Price (USD)')\naxes[0].legend(fontsize=10)\naxes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\naxes[0].xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%b %Y'))\n\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('transformer_predictions.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-23T05:06:03.761143Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-23T05:06:03.761784Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-23T05:06:04.573603Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-23T05:06:03.761757Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-23T05:06:04.572718Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1680x1200 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":61},{"id":"l8-hdr","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## LSTM Step 8 — Define LSTM Architecture\n\n```\nInput (batch, 60, 5)\n  │\n  ├─ LSTM(128, return_sequences=True)  ← captures long-range dependencies\n  ├─ Dropout(0.2)\n  ├─ LSTM(64, return_sequences=False)  ← condenses temporal context\n  ├─ Dropout(0.2)\n  ├─ Dense(32, relu)\n  └─ Dense(1)  ← predicted Close price\n```","metadata":{}},{"id":"l8-code","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── LSTM Step 8: Define LSTM Architecture ───────────────────────────────────────\ndef build_lstm(seq_len, n_features,\n               units_1=128, units_2=64, dropout_rate=0.2):\n    \"\"\"\n    Stacked Bidirectional-ready LSTM for time-series forecasting.\n    Input  → LSTM(128, seq) → Dropout → LSTM(64) → Dropout → Dense(32) → Dense(1)\n    \"\"\"\n    model = keras.Sequential([\n        keras.Input(shape=(seq_len, n_features), name='input'),\n\n        # ── First LSTM layer: return sequences for stacking ─────────────────────\n        layers.LSTM(units_1, return_sequences=True,\n                    kernel_regularizer=keras.regularizers.l2(1e-4),\n                    name='lstm_1'),\n        layers.Dropout(dropout_rate, name='dropout_1'),\n\n        # ── Second LSTM layer: returns final hidden state only ──────────────────\n        layers.LSTM(units_2, return_sequences=False,\n                    kernel_regularizer=keras.regularizers.l2(1e-4),\n                    name='lstm_2'),\n        layers.Dropout(dropout_rate, name='dropout_2'),\n\n        # ── Regression head ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n        layers.Dense(32, activation='relu', name='dense_1'),\n        layers.Dense(1,  name='output')\n    ], name='LSTM_Forecaster')\n\n    return model\n\n\nlstm_model = build_lstm(seq_len=SEQ, n_features=N_FEATURES)\nlstm_model.summary()\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-23T05:10:07.616735Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-23T05:10:07.617173Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-23T05:10:07.681523Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-23T05:10:07.617147Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-23T05:10:07.680964Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"\u001b[1mModel: \"LSTM_Forecaster\"\u001b[0m\n","text/html":"<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier Ne